Custom Naive Bayes Classifier from Scratch¶

This notebook implements a Gaussian Naive Bayes classifier from scratch using Python and NumPy, without sklearn.
We also compare its accuracy with sklearn's GaussianNB on the breast_cancer dataset**.

Naive Bayes Overview¶

Naive Bayes is a probabilistic classifier based on Bayes’ Theorem:

$ { P(C_k | X) = \frac{P(X | C_k) \cdot P(C_k)}{P(X)} } $

  • $C_k $ = class
  • $X = [x_1, x_2, ..., x_n] $= feature vector
  • Assumes feature independence (naive assumption)

For continuous features, we use a Gaussian likelihood:

$ { P(x_i | C_k) = \frac{1}{\sqrt{2 \pi \sigma_k^2}} \exp\left(-\frac{(x_i - \mu_k)^2}{2 \sigma_k^2}\right) } $ where $\mu_k $ and $ \sigma_k^2 $ are the mean and variance of the feature for class (C_k).
